Storytime: 
Okay guys first.. there are SO many pigeons in Porto and Rachel shames me every time I want to pet one 😭I will pet one of these days I swear🤣
SECOND.. the universe has so many different ways of telling you you’re in the perfect place at the perfect time. The way the universe will just give you anything you ask. I truly feel lucky🤞🏼 
The fact that I booked my bus ticket for the wrong date and this man was nice enough to not leave me in the rain at the bus stop in the middle on Europe was amazing😭 
And the way me & Rachel are literally staying on AUGUST 24th street….. if u know you know. That one shook me to my bones. 

So excited about what’s to come 🤍

What should me and Rachel do while we’re in Barcelona?

I miss my mom already 😭 but BARCELONA DAY 1 🇪🇸
-
Storytime: 
Okay okay so now I’m starting to notice the differences between everyday life in the US and Europe 🤣

FIRST: the LAST thing these ppl will drink is a glass of water 😭 I swear I’ve neva been more dehydrated ever! 

SECOND: I LOVEEE how people love to talk here. I’m a talkative ass person so being around ppl who genuinely want to know about you and your life is so welcoming and fun! And I love all the different accents of everyone Omgg😏

THIRD: I LOVE walking! I think just aimlessly walking the city streets in a cute outfit is my new fav hobby. Finding cute little hole in the wall gems and chilling with locals fills my heart up I can’t explain it 🥺 think I might need to move cus I never wanna leave.
-
Going to start posting more little moment reels instead of whole day vlogs, dw I’ll still make them but small moments are more personal :) 
-
LOVE U FRIENDS 🤍

I only wish I can add all of 2023’s moments 😭
-
I want to say thank you to the universe for allowing me to experience all the amazing moments of this year. I’ve met amazing people, I’ve tried amazing food, I stepped out of my comfort zone, and I got a bit clearer on the life I want. 
-
This year has honestly been the MOST mentally challenging (uncertainty, insecurity, adversity & intense healing) but also the most rewarding physically (traveling, graduating life coaching school, buying my car, my page growing by 20,000 of you!). 
-
I am so grateful for the ups and downs of this year. They have taught me to be tough and to also give myself grace for when I’m not feeling that tough. Everything is a balance and a learning experience. 
-
I can only say that in 2024 we are focusing of being genuinely happy and moving with intention, no more drowning in a glass of water for me.
-
Cheers to 2024! 🤍
